SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 635
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Dewey
Branstetter, Jr., to the Tennessee Ethics
Commission.
WHEREAS, pursuant to Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 3-6-103, Governor Bill Lee
has selected Dewey Branstetter, Jr., as his appointee from the minority party to the Tennessee
Ethics Commission; and
WHEREAS, Dewey Branstetter, Jr., is a partner at Sherrard Roe in Nashville, where he
concentrates his legal practice on utility and municipal issues, including employee benefits
issues and other complex litigation; and
WHEREAS, he has represented utility districts and municipalities; assisted public entities
with planning pensions, insurance, and other health and welfare programs; and represented
both employees and employers in disputes; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of Vanderbilt University Law School, Mr. Branstetter has earned
numerous accolades throughout his career, and he has served his community as a member of
numerous boards and foundations; currently, he serves as chairman of the Metro Nashville
Charter Revision Commission; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 3-6-103, requires that each
gubernatorial appointee be confirmed by a two-thirds (2/3) vote of approval by each house of
the General Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that this body hereby confirms the appointment of
SJR0635
011597
- 1 -

Dewey Branstetter, Jr., to the Tennessee Ethics Commission, such term to expire on December
31, 2028.
